  "response": "To become an IAS (Indian Administrative Service) officer, you need to:\n\n1. Eligibility Criteria:\n- Graduate degree from a recognized university\n- Age limit: 21-32 years (with age relaxations for reserved categories)\n- Clear the UPSC Civil Services Examination\n\n2. Academic Performance:\n- Your 10th and 12th percentages are good\n- However, UPSC selection depends primarily on:\n  a) Graduation percentage\n  b) Civil Services Exam performance\n  c) Interview scores\n\n3. Civil Services Exam Process:\n- Preliminary Exam (Objective)\n- Main Exam (Written)\n- Personality Test/Interview\n\n4. Preparation Tips:\n- Study NCERT books\n- Follow current affairs\n- Practice previous years' question papers\n- Take mock tests\n- Choose optional subject wisely\n\n5. Important Points:\n- Academic marks are not the sole criteria\n- Comprehensive preparation is key\n- Consistent hard work matters most\n\nYour academic scores look good. Focus on overall preparation for the UPSC Civil Services Examination to increase your chances of becoming an IAS officer.",
